text.section:
Prisoners confined in the penitentiaries shall not be required to work outside of the walls or enclosures of the prison except:
On the construction or maintenance of public roads and bridges;
On the making and preparing of materials for public roads and bridges;
On work upon the public works of the state;
On state farms; or
During pestilence or in the case of the destruction of prison buildings when such prisoners cannot be confined within the prison walls or enclosures.
